>If you have an on-line copy of the dictionnary, then you can do the
>following:
>
>  grep -i e /usr/dict/words | wc
>
>... to find how many words contain the letter 'e'.  You can do this for all
>26 letters.  This is the results I got with a dictionary of 25144 words:
>
... stuff deleted...

>Norman.
>-- 

This gives the frequency within words, but may or may not be representative of the 
frequency of letters within text of the type under analysis, since words are not
uniformly distributed throughout text.  You may need different freqency tables
depending on the type of message/text under attack.
